parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause coolant leaks, overheating, and electrical problems, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or vehicle damage.
symptoms: Coolant leaking from underneath the dashboard
coolant spraying on the occupants
smoke and sparks coming from the vehicle
the heater core running hotter than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Windshield damage can impair the driver's visibility, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Cracked windshield
windshield leaks causing rust damage and electrical problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine and other components, and potentially causing a loss of vehicle control or an accident.
symptoms: Smoke coming from the cooling system area
antifreeze odor present in the passenger compartment
radiator leak.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood hinges can cause the hood to suddenly open while driving, obstructing the driver's view and potentially leading to accidents or injuries. In severe cases, the hood can break off and cause further damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The hood unexpectedly opens or flies up while driving
the hood breaks off
the hood hinges break or show signs of stress or fatigue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The roof collapse can cause serious injury or death to occupants in the event of a rollover accident.
symptoms: The roof collapses or crushes in a rollover accident
the vehicle loses control and overturns
the roof structure fails to provide adequate protection to occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to engage gears properly can cause the vehicle to unexpectedly shift into the wrong gear, leading to loss of control, accidents, or damage to the transmission.
symptoms: The vehicle gears will not go into reverse
instead shifting into first gear
the driveshaft disconnects from the transmission
the vehicle is prone to being shifted into the wrong gear
especially when 1st gear and reverse are parallel to each other.
